```import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Data
strength_data = np.array([5.9, 7.2, 7.3, 6.3, 8.1, 6.8, 7.0, 7.6, 6.8, 6.5,
                          7.0, 6.3, 7.9, 9.0, 8.2, 8.7, 7.8, 9.7, 7.4, 7.7,
                          9.7, 7.8, 7.7, 11.6, 11.3, 11.8, 10.7])

# A) Stem-and-leaf plot approximation
def stem_plot(data):
    stems = {}
    for number in data:
        stem, leaf = divmod(int(number*10), 10)
        if stem not in stems:
            stems[stem] = []
        stems[stem].append(leaf)

    # Sorting and printing the stems and leaves
    for stem in sorted(stems.keys()):
        print(f"{stem} | {' '.join(map(str, sorted(stems[stem])))}")

stem_plot(strength_data)

# B) Histogram of the data
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))
plt.hist(strength_data, bins=10, color='lightblue', edgecolor='black')
plt.title("Histogram of Flexural Strength Data")
plt.xlabel("Strength (MPa)")
plt.ylabel("Frequency")
plt.show()

# C) Boxplot to check for outliers
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))
plt.boxplot(strength_data, vert=False, patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor="lightgreen"))
plt.title("Boxplot of Flexural Strength Data")
plt.xlabel("Strength (MPa)")
plt.show()

# D) Proportion of values exceeding 10 MPa
exceed_10_mpa = np.sum(strength_data > 10) / len(strength_data)
exceed_10_mpa
```
